76561198051384176,Recommended,428200,22425850,"Posted: 15 April, 2016",all,♋️LunarCainEX🐶,Played an hour on offline (Doing some system config) and currently playing online at the time of this review. (Also stuck on a certain level due to a Combo Condition)+The game is actually an very interesting concept with funny artistic character designs taken from Chinese History and Characters from Romance of the Three Kingdoms. The only catch is that its like a parody with genderbender with some of them (Guan Yu&Zhang Fei are Female but not Lui Bei). Thus the reason you see chinese characters in the game itself.+Its quite beautiful and alive especially the visual effects and its perspective view of 2.5 and 3D. Think of Muramasa: The Demon Blade game if you have played it on the DS or VITA.+Don't worry for the game is fully in English with some funny translation but the Developers are Chinese so its bound to have funny translation.+The Music is also quite amusing to listen since it fits the gameplay. The gameplay itself is situated as a button turn base where you choose the 1 abilities per turn per characters. You can score points by racking up the combo whilst dealing more damage and staggering the enemies so they can't counter attack. Its all about timing.+The map is like Mario where you travel in each node.-/+You can level up each characters with coins you earn from your travels though it will be grinding/farming since you need to level them up just to pass a level.-/+To unlock characters you not only need to get through a certain part of the story but you need certain number of stars to unlock them.+Gamepad is supported though I only tested using X-Input so I have no clue about D-Input.-There are some minor bugs to be found though its nothing Game breaking.-/+Some dialog when playing in English weren't translated but they will fix it next month.
,Recommended,428200,22422300,"Posted: 14 April, 2016",all,=AJSA= 不歸V.I.Dread黃泉,"Outstanding game! This truelly is a gem for all who love fast pase, thinking 2 steps ahead, cute cartoony character beat em up games... BUT! This game have a slight twist then the normal beat em up game...There are no direct control of your hero's movement, they taking turns jump into then fight then withdraw when the next hero enter the battle, and the control have been split for both left and right hand...Left hand WASD = Controlls the roaster of heroes in your team, game will auto rotate your heroes if no extra command was given, but you can use WASD keys to force select a hero from your roaster so you can unleash one of his skill that is not in cooldown.Right hand IHJK = Controlls the 4 skills of each hero. J is the basic attack, that every heroes start with at lv1. K is advanced tier attack, and H is higher tier attack, Heroes unlock this 2 at higher level. I is ultimate attack, and also the last skill to be unlocked, they are not just dealing large amount of damage, they also laster way longer then any other attacks, and the lasting effect extend into 1-2 more heroes's turn.The goal of this game is to plan and form combos with the attacks of your heroes, and use those attack to ether stunlock or push back waves of enemy, but enemy do have special ability or will be located at areas that some attacks just won't be able to touch them, so it will be up to the player to form up a team of heroes to bring down those annony buggers.This game have a really fast gaming pace, really nice graphic for an indie game, funky cartoony design... It is fun to play, and even the music make me want to record it for my MP3 player!!Okie.. I forgot to mention the down side... Due to this is a Chinese indie game, so far only some of the dialogues (most of them) and menus were translated into English, other in-game signs like ""Let The Battle Begin!"", ""Show them what you can do!"" and ""Victory!"" are still in Chinese... So it might be eyesore for some Internet Nazi, but not a big issue for normal game player. :P"
